'''Si''' 思 is a concept in [[Chinese philosophy]] that is usually translated as "reflection" or "concentration." It refers to a species of attentive, non-[[Rationality|rational]] [[thought]] that is directed at a specific subject.<ref>Ivanhoe, P.J., & Van Norden, B.W. (eds.) (2001). ''Readings in Classical Chinese Philosophy'', 2nd Ed. Hackett Publishing Co.: Indianapolis, p. 392</ref>
